						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Śrīvallabha, 34th year = c. 14th Century.</p>						

						<p>Badly mutilated. The trustees of the Tiruvēṅgaivāyil temple seem to have assigned some temple land to an individual with the condition that he should pay some specified quantity of paddy annually after reclaiming it for cultivation.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 640.]</p>						

